{
  "texts": [
    "-Simplifying the relationship between CSS, drugs and cancers may have obscured intricate linkages.",
    "-The model's effectiveness depended heavily on the quality and representation of its underlying dataset.",
    "-Seeing some drugs repeated across cancers raised questions about bias and generalizability.",
    "-The lack of external validation with new data left applicability to other scenarios uncertain.",
    "The proposed framework highlighted the importance of drug mechanisms in drug combination therapy decisions."
  ]
}